Database Foundations for Business Analytics

BUAN 6320

Naveen Jindal School of Management

This course covers Structured Query Language (SQL) and NoSQL databases and focuses on understanding the differences and learning how to query SQL and NoSQL databases effectively. Topics include ER models, SQL, mapping an ER model to a relational schema, NoSQL database types, and NoSQL querying. Credit cannot be received for more than one of the following: BUAN 6320 or SYSM 6338 or MIS 6326 or ACCT 6320 or ACCT 6321 or MIS 6320 or OPRE 6393. 3 credit hours.

Offering Frequency: Each semester

Grades: 6,616

Median GPA: A-

Mean GPA: 3.618
